The [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]] was surrounded by a dense '''[[Comet/Legends|comet]] cloud''', remnants from the system's formation. Most of the comets followed erratic courses around the system, some of which had dense cores similar to the system's heavier planets.<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

They interacted with each other resulting in occasional collisions, showering frozen debris resulting in the creation of smaller comets.

The comet cloud was sometimes known to cause interruptions in [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] travel. This was an annoyance to some of the system's inhabitants, though also contributed to the system's defenses.<ref name="LFC" />

[[Brin Hesk'l]]'s ship was once found floating abandoned in the comet cloud.<ref name="ITW">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/livingforce/swlf20040715|text=Into the Woods}}</ref>

